    {
      "type": "example",
      "content_latex": "Example 15\n\nWrite as a single fraction:\n\n(a) $\\frac{x}{6} + \\frac{x-2}{3}$\n\n(b) $\\frac{x+1}{2} - \\frac{x-2}{3}$\n\nSolutions:\n\n(a) $\\frac{x}{6} + \\frac{x-2}{3}$\n$= \\frac{x}{6} + \\frac{2}{2}\\left(\\frac{x-2}{3}\\right)$\n$= \\frac{x + 2(x-2)}{6}$\n$= \\frac{x + 2x - 4}{6}$\n$= \\frac{3x - 4}{6}$\n\n(b) $\\frac{x+1}{2} - \\frac{x-2}{3}$\n$= \\frac{3}{3}\\left(\\frac{x+1}{2}\\right) - \\frac{2}{2}\\left(\\frac{x-2}{3}\\right)$\n$= \\frac{3(x+1)}{6} - \\frac{2(x-2)}{6}$\n$= \\frac{3(x+1) - 2(x-2)}{6}$\n$= \\frac{3x + 3 - 2x + 4}{6}$\n$= \\frac{x + 7}{6}$",
      "source_images": ["image282.png"]
